  "texts": [
    "Indeed, since Āω • + ε attains its maximum among the active part of the population and its minimum among the inactive part, active individuals are the most likely to interact.Since the Fokker-Planck model is less complex than its integro-differential counterpart (11), we are now also able to study the evolution of the mass fractions of each part of the population and of the average activity level.",
    "Sinced dt ρ a (t) = λ A (ω p + ε -a p) ∫ I f (t, γ, w)dw,(17)d dt ρ i (t) = -λ A (ε -a p) ∫ I f (t, -γ, w)dw,(18)the different ranges of values to which a p belongs (cases (i)-(iii) described at the beginning of the section) lead to different situations (recall that ∂ t ρ u = -∂ t ρ a -∂ t ρ i):• case (i): ρ a increases, ρ i decreases and ρ u can show different behaviors depending on the initial distribution;• case (ii): ρ a and ρ i increase, therefore ρ u decreases due to the conservation of the total mass;• case (iii): ρ a decreases, ρ i increases and ρ u can show different behaviors depending on the initial distribution.",
